<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1898-02-17T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1898-02-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="968" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d968">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Woodford</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Sherman</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Madrid</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1898-02-17"><hi rend="italic">February 17,
                                    1898</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 143.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Late yesterday afternoon, February 16, I
                            received the reply of the Spanish Government, dated February 15 instant,
                            to my note of <pb facs="1110" n="1014" xml:id="pg_1014"/> February 14,
                            relating to Señor Dupuy de Lôme and his letter of last December.</p>
                        <p>By working all night we have succeeded in completing translation of same,
                            and I have just telegraphed you giving full text of my translation.</p>
                        <p>Such telegram is as follows:<note n="1" xml:id="d968fn1">Not printed; see
                                inclosure with No. 147.</note></p>
                        <p>I inclose complete copy of the Spanish text,<note n="1" xml:id="d968fn2">Not printed; see inclosure with No. 147.</note> so that the
                            Department may revise my translation as given in the telegram repeated
                            above.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Stewart L. Woodford.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>